    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear offensive engine, led by **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against a fading Quintana, while **Gunnar Henderson** thrives on a combination of wind-out conditions and an ideal spot in the order against Lugo. The matchup against Elder is particularly fruitful for our middle infield, where **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Brady House** (60.72) are locked into strong, high-upside scoring tiers. While **Dominic Smith** (60.09) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) benefit significantly from facing Irvin\u2019s high xERA of 4.92, we remain cautious with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (55.26), whose upside is tempered by a daunting matchup against the talented Reid Detmers.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo**, who finished with a respectable 50.81. While **Coby Mayo** remains a high-variance asset, the optimizer prioritized the consistent efficiency of **Nasim Nunez** (53.38) and the overall depth of the starting lineup. We continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill**, both of whom are unavailable today due to team off-days, forcing us to lean heavily on the remaining active roster. Strategic risks remain, specifically with our reliance on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Gunnar Henderson**. Should the official lineups shift these players down in the batting order, their daily efficiency scores will be subject to immediate downward revision.",
